  "wikitext": "The following terms are used when considering the conspicuity of AtoN lights at night.\n\n{|\n|-\n! Term !! Definition\n|-\n| Detection of an AtoN light:|| The observer is aware of a light\n|-\n| Recognition of an AtoN light:|| The observer is aware that the light is an AtoN light\n|-\n| Identification of an AtoN light:|| The observer is aware of the exact AtoN to which the light belongs\n|-\n| Confirmation of an AtoN light:|| The observer identifies the flash character of the signal once again, to verify\n|}\n\n\n\n\n\nSource: ENG7, Guideline G1073\n\n{{languages|Codes on Alerts and Indicators}}\n[[Category:2.1 Optics and Vision]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 2018 Revision]]\n[[Category:Approved by Council through approval of source document]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 2023 Revision]]"
